<subSubSection id="C306789DFFCFFF9E6BB0FC92FF36FB3D" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFCFFF9E6BB0FC92FAF0FBAD" blockId="5.[151,1436,860,1173]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6BB0FC92FE54FCDC" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[151,394,860,884]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericeus">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6BB0FC92FE54FCDC" box="[151,394,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Camponotus sericeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the more common carpenter ants of the Arabian Peninsula (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6F90FC92FA49FCDD" author="Collingwood, C. A." box="[1207,1431,860,885]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="230 - 302" refId="ref6815" refString="Collingwood, C. A. (1985) Hymenoptera: Fam. Formicidae of Saudi Arabia. Fauna Saudi Arabia, 7, 230 - 302." type="journal article" year="1985">Collingwood, 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6BB0FCB1FE2AFC30" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D." box="[151,500,895,920]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="300 - 385" refId="ref6843" refString="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. (1996) Formicidae of Saudi Arabia (Part 2). Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 15, 300 - 385." type="journal article" year="1996">Collingwood and Agosti, 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6AD8FCB1FCCDFC30" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. &amp; Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T." box="[511,787,895,920]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="405 - 474" refId="ref6877" refString="Collingwood, C. A., Agosti, D., Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T. (2011) Order Hymenoptera, Family Formicidae. Arthropod Fauna of the UAE, 4, 405 - 474." type="journal article" year="2011">
Collingwood 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E69BEFC4FFD0FFC30" box="[665,721,895,920]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). It was originally described from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6FB2FCB1FB2EFC30" box="[1173,1264,895,920]" name="Senegal" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Senegal</collectingCountry>
, recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6BB0FC6AFF35FC15" box="[151,235,932,957]" name="Algeria" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Algeria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6BDCFC6AFE72FC15" author="Santschi, F." box="[251,428,932,957]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="97 - 108" refId="ref8132" refString="Santschi, F. (1929 a) Fourmis du Sahara central recoltees par la Mission du Hoggar. Bulletin de la Societ d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord, 20, 97 - 108." type="journal article" year="1929">Santschi 1929a</bibRefCitation>
) and has a broad distribution throughout the Afrotropical region (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6F86FC6AFA98FC15" author="Wheeler, W. M." box="[1185,1350,932,957]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="1 - 1139" refId="ref9300" refString="Wheeler, W. M. (1922) Ants of the American Museum Congo Expedition. A contribution to the myrmecology of Africa. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 45, 1 - 1139." type="journal article" year="1922">Wheeler 1922</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6E74FC6AFF0AFC48" author="Taylor, B." pageId="5" pageNumber="570" refId="ref8914" refString="Taylor, B. (2010) Ants of Africa. Tenth Edition. Available from: http: // antbase. org / ants / africa (Accessed 13 Dec. 2012)" type="url" year="2010">Taylor 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Additional records are from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6914FC09FD4CFC48" box="[563,658,967,992]" name="Pakistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6984FC09FCA0FC48" author="Umair, M. &amp; Zia, A. &amp; Naeem, M. &amp; Chaudhry, M. T." box="[675,894,967,992]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="699 - 705" refId="ref9176" refString="Umair, M., Zia, A., Naeem, M. &amp; Chaudhry, M. T. (2012) Species composition of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in Potohar Plateau of Punjab Province, Pakistan. Pakistan Journal of Zoology, 44, 699 - 705." type="journal article" year="2012">
Umair 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E69D1FC07FCECFC48" box="[758,818,967,992]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">et al.</emphasis>
, 2012
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E68B3FC09FC0EFC48" box="[916,976,967,992]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">India</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6F36FC09FBBCFC48" box="[1041,1122,967,992]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6F54FC09FA8AFC48" author="Collingwood, C. A." box="[1139,1364,967,992]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="3 - 4" refId="ref6786" refString="Collingwood, C. A. (1962) Some ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from North-East Asia. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 83, 3 - 4." type="journal article" year="1962">Collingwood, 1962</bibRefCitation>
). This species has also been reported from the Oriental region, 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6829FC23FCE8FBAC" box="[782,822,1005,1028]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">e.g.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E681AFC22FC7FFBAD" box="[829,929,1004,1029]" name="Thailand" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6888FC22FAFCFBAD" author="Jaitrong, W. &amp; Nabhitabhata, J." box="[943,1314,1004,1029]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="9 - 54" refId="ref7647" refString="Jaitrong, W. &amp; Nabhitabhata, J. (2005) A list of known ant species of Thailand (Formicidae: Hymenoptera). The Thailand Natural History Museum Journal, 1, 9 - 54. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1206 / 355.1" type="journal article" year="2005">Jaitrong and Nabhitabhata, 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFCFFF9E6BE0FBC1FF36FB3D" blockId="5.[151,1436,860,1173]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
Workers are active throughout Rawdhat Khorim, being abundant from March through October, with a major peak in June. Workers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6A9FFBFAFDEBFBE4" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[440,565,1076,1100]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericeus">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6A9FFBFAFDEBFBE4" box="[440,565,1076,1100]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">C. sericeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur on 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6981FBFAFD2AFBE3" box="[678,756,1076,1099]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6981FBFAFD2AFBE3" box="[678,756,1076,1099]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Acacia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
trees and on the giant milkweed 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6F4BFBFAFEFAFBD8" authority="(Aiton) W. T. Aiton" authorityName="W. T. Aiton" baseAuthorityName="Aiton" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Calotropis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6F4BFBFAFA9FFBE4" box="[1132,1345,1076,1101]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Calotropis procera</emphasis>
(Aiton) W. T. Aiton
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6A11FB99FE0AFBD8" box="[310,468,1111,1136]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Apocynaceae</taxonomicName>
). Several workers have been observed foraging on 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6F0BFB96FB77FBD8" box="[1068,1193,1112,1136]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Calotropis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6F0BFB96FB77FBD8" box="[1068,1193,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">C. procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
plants and attending aphids.
</paragraph>
